\@writefile{lot}{\contentsline {table}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Full erasure method comparison at layer 8 across three concept domains. Each method's $\lambda ^*$ is selected from the same grid $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation nonlinear probe accuracy, ensuring a fair comparison where every method gets its best shot at erasure. L/NL Leak: retrained linear logistic-regression / nonlinear MLP probe accuracy (lower = better concept removal). $\Delta $Ctrl: downstream control task accuracy change relative to clean representations (closer to zero = more surgical). Rem\%: fraction of concept-correlated SAE features disrupted ($\delta {>}2\%$; higher = better erasure). Dmg\%: fraction of non-concept SAE features with $>{10}\%$ activation change (lower = less collateral damage). Rdst\%: fraction of non-concept features that become concept-correlated post-erasure (lower = less reshuffling). Model: Qwen2.5-0.5B. SAE: $64\times $ TopK, $k{=}64$. Control tasks: answer matching (sycophancy), profession classification (gender), helpfulness (safety).}}{8}{table.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{tab:full_comparison}{{2}{8}{Full erasure method comparison at layer 8 across three concept domains. Each method's $\lambda ^*$ is selected from the same grid $\{0.5, 1.0, 2.0, 4.0, 8.0\}$ by lowest validation nonlinear probe accuracy, ensuring a fair comparison where every method gets its best shot at erasure. L/NL Leak: retrained linear logistic-regression / nonlinear MLP probe accuracy (lower = better concept removal). $\Delta $Ctrl: downstream control task accuracy change relative to clean representations (closer to zero = more surgical). Rem\%: fraction of concept-correlated SAE features disrupted ($\delta {>}2\%$; higher = better erasure). Dmg\%: fraction of non-concept SAE features with $>{10}\%$ activation change (lower = less collateral damage). Rdst\%: fraction of non-concept features that become concept-correlated post-erasure (lower = less reshuffling). Model: Qwen2.5-0.5B. SAE: $64\times $ TopK, $k{=}64$. Control tasks: answer matching (sycophancy), profession classification (gender), helpfulness (safety)}{table.2}{}}
